						               													<description>This game is part of the &amp;quot;Lukas Podolski game series&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are green and white circles on the board which are connected with white lines with numbers on it.&amp;#10;Each player gets a deck in one color (black or red) and draws four cards. The player that wins the toss begins the game. To pass the ball the player has to play a card with the number equal or higher than the number on the white lines. If a player plays the ball to a white circle he/she can play another card. Otherwise there is a duel between the two players.&amp;#10;Duel:&amp;#10;Each player has four cards (if a player doesn't have four cards, complete the cards, till you have four) Then both player place a card on the table, face down. When both players have chosen a crad, turn around the cards. The player with the highest number on the card, has ball control. That player can pass the ball along the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To score points, the player plays the number (or a higher number) indicated on the board in front of the goal. To keep track of the points, a player receives a goal-chip each time a goal is made. If a player runs out of cards, the player with the most points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
